BBC Music magazine (October 2014)

ISSN: 0966-7180 | 118 pages | PDF


BBC Music Magazine is a must for anyone with a passion for classical music.  Classical music connoisseurs and new enthusiast alike will enjoy the fascinating features and reviews of over 120 new works in every issue, including sections on jazz and world music.


IN THE OCTOBER ISSUE:

* To mark Radio 3's Brahms festival this autumn, we delve inside the life and work of the great Romantic composer Johannes Brahms -- an enigmatic figure, his music was coloured by his complex personality, love of 18th-century music and lunchtime trips to the pub;

* Ten top performers name their favourite Brahms work;

* 200 years after the birth of Adolphe Sax, Mervyn Cook looks at the impact that his invention, the saxophone, has had on music;

* James Naughtie meets the four members of the esteemed British vocal group, The Hilliard Ensemble;

* and David Owen Norris looks at how obituaries can make or break a composer's reputation.

